            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Hd1e108">Rubrica 14</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De auaritia et cupiditate pecunie</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e114">
               <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>
      ¶ De auaritia cupiditate pecunie
      <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>Rubrica. 14
    </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e121"> 
      !--226.xml--&gt;
      <pb ed="#V" n="94-r"/>
               <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e122">IN exodo c. 20.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e129">Non 
               con<lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>cupisces 
               do<lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>mum proximi tui: nec desideres 
               vxo<lb ed="#V" n="4" break="no"/>rem eius: non seruum non ancillam
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>non ouem nec bouem: non asinum: nec 
               om<lb ed="#V" n="6" break="no"/>nia que illius sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e143">
               <lb ed="#V" n="7"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e142">In leuitico. c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e147">Cum messueris segetes 
               ter<lb ed="#V" n="8" break="no"/>re tue non tondebis vsque ad solum 
               superfi<lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>ciem terre: nec remanentes spicas colliges:
        <lb ed="#V" n="10"/>neque in vinea tua racemos et grana 
               deciden<lb ed="#V" n="11" break="no"/>tia congregabis: sed pauperibus et peregrinis
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>carpenda dimittes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e162">
               <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e163">Salomon in prouerbiis. c. 15.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e166">Conturbat
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>domum suam qui sectatur auaritiam.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e172"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e173">Idem
        <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>in ecclesias. c. 15.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e174">Auarus non implebitur pecunia
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>et qui amat diuitias fructus non capiet ex eis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e182">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e188">Abacuch propheta. c. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e186">Ue qui congregat
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>auaritiam malam domui sue.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e192">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e200">Cronica de nugis philosophorum. c. 24
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>scilicet de bione.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e196">Bio ad pusilanimem diuitem ait:
        <lb ed="#V" n="21"/>Non hic possidet opes: sed opes eum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e204">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e215">Aristotelis retho. li. i. c. 19.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e208">Accidit 
               pauperi<lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>bus propter indigentiam concupiscere 
               pe<lb ed="#V" n="24" break="no"/>cunias: diuitibus autem propter <unclear>ptantem</unclear><!--potentiam?--> 
               con<lb ed="#V" n="25" break="no"/>cupiscere nisi necessarias delectationes.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e218"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e232">Li.
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>2. c. 16</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e220">Iuuenes minime sunt amatores 
               pe<lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>cuniarum propterea quod nondum 
               indigenti<lb ed="#V" n="28" break="no"/>am experti sunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e231"> 
       / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e248">Idem <sic>pollyticorum:</sic> li. 2
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e233">Malitia hominum irreplebilis est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e239">
               <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>
               / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e263">Idem ethicorum: li. 4. c. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e243">Pecunias 
               dici<lb ed="#V" n="31" break="no"/>mus omnia quorumcumque dignitas 
               munisma<lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>te mensuratur. Prodigus multum videtur
        <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>melior esse illiberali: quoniam hic quidem prodest
        <lb ed="#V" n="34"/>multis: hic autem nulli: sed nec in seipsum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e255">
               <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>
               / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e281">Illiberalitas insanabilis est.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e259">Uidetur 
               se<lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>nectus et omnis impotentia illiberales 
               face<lb ed="#V" n="37" break="no"/>re: magis connaturalis est hominibus 
               prodi<lb ed="#V" n="38" break="no"/>galitate. multi enim amatores pecuniarum
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>magis quam datores</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e271"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e297">Idem magnorum 
               morali<lb ed="#V" n="40" break="no"/>um: li. i. c. 42.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e273">Illiberalis est: qui non 
               consu<lb ed="#V" n="41" break="no"/>mit in que oportet: et quecunque oportet et
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>quando oportet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e283">
               <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e314">Iesus filius sirach in ecclesiast. c. 10.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e287">
               Ni<lb ed="#V" n="44" break="no"/>hil est iniquius quam amare pecuniam. Hic enim
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>animam suam venalem habet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e295"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e326">18. c.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e297">Ui <!--226.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46" break="no"/>ro cupido et tenaci sine ratione est 
               substan<lb ed="#V" n="47" break="no"/>tia. Qui aceruat ex animo suo iniuste aliis
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>congregat: et in bonis illius alius luxuriabitur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>Qui sibi nequaem est cui alii bonus erit: et non 
               io<lb ed="#V" n="50" break="no"/>cundabitur in bonis suis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e317">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e352">Terentius in adelphis. c. 26</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e321">Uicium commune 
               omni<lb ed="#V" n="52" break="no"/>um est quod nimium ad rem in senecta attenti sumus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e327">
               <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e364">Salustius in catilinario</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e331">Auaritia fidem
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>probitatem ceterasque bonas artes 
               subuer<lb ed="#V" n="55" break="no"/>tit. pro his superbiam crudelitatem deos 
               ne<lb ed="#V" n="56" break="no"/>gligere omnia venalia habere docuit. 
               Aua<lb ed="#V" n="57" break="no"/>ricia semper infinita insaciabilis est: neque 
               co<lb ed="#V" n="58" break="no"/>pia: neque inopia minuitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e345">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e384">Uirgilius enied. li. 3 in pri.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e349">Quid non 
               mor<lb ed="#V" n="60" break="no"/>talia pectora cogis Auri sacra fames.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e355">
               <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e396">Oratius in epistolis l. i. e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e359">Feruet auaritia 
               mi<lb ed="#V" n="62" break="no"/>seraque cupidine pectus. Sunt verba et voces 
               qui<lb ed="#V" n="63" break="no"/>bus hunc lenire dolorem Possis: et morbi 
               ma<lb ed="#V" n="64" break="no"/>gnam deponere partem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e369"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e410">Epistola. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e371">Quod est cui contingit nil amplius optet. Semper 
               aua<lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>rus eget: certum voto pete finem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e379"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e422">Epistola. 5.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="67"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e381">Parcus ob heredis curam nimiumque seuerus
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Assidet insano.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e390"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e435">Epistola. 10</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e392">Imperat aut seruit collecta pecunia cuique</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e398">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e447">Libro. 2 epistola. 3. et fi.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="71"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e402">Quanto plura parasti: Tanto plura cupis</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e408">
               <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>
             ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e459">Tullius de oratore: li. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e412">Auaritiam si 
               tolle<lb ed="#V" n="73" break="no"/>re vultis mater est tollenda luxuries.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e418"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e469">Idem
        <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>retho. artis noue: lib. 2. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e420">Auaritia hominem
        <lb ed="#V" n="75"/>ad quoduis maleficium impellit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e428"> 
         /  <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e482">Lib. 5. c. 21.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e430">Auaritia est iniuriosa appetitio alienorum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e436">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e494">Li. 6. et fi. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e440">Due res que possunt homines
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/>ad turpem compendium commouere: inopia atque
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>auaritia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e449"> 
       / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e507">Idem paradoxorum prima distinctione.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e451">Neque expletur vnquam nec saciatur cupiditas sit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e457">
               <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e519">Ouidius fastorum: libro i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e461">Tempore creuit amor qui
        <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>nunc est summus habendi. Uix vltra quo iam 
               progre<lb ed="#V" n="83" break="no"/>diatur habet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e469"> 
       / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e531">Idem de ponto: li. 4. et fi. e. 15. et pe.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e471">Res moderata cupido est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e477">
               <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e543">Quintillianus declamationum. 14 declam.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e481">Omnia facinora nisi fallor causas vel de 
               cupi<lb ed="#V" n="87" break="no"/>ditate vel de simultatibus trahunt.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e489">
               <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e557">Iacobus apostolus epistola vnica. c. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e493">Unde 
               bel<lb ed="#V" n="89" break="no"/>la et lites inter vos nonne hinc ex concupiscentiis
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/>vestris que militant in membris vestris. <!--227.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="94-v"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e507">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e577">Paulus apostolus epistola. i. ad 
               thimo<lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>teum. c. 6. et fina</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e511">Radix omnium malorum
        <lb ed="#V" n="3"/>est cupiditas.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e520"> 
            / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e591">Idem epistola ad hebreos
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>c. 13. et fina.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e522">Sint mores sine auaritia 
               con<lb ed="#V" n="5" break="no"/>tenti presentibus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e602">   
        <lb ed="#V" n="6"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e606">Seneca in epistolis ad lucillum: li. 7. e. i.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="7"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e610">Nemo se auarum esse intelligit neque 
               cupi<lb ed="#V" n="8" break="no"/>dum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e536"> 
         / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e618">Libro. 6. e. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e538">Auarus quomodo 
               pe<lb ed="#V" n="9" break="no"/>cunia vtendum sit non exaudit. Auarus 
               ani<lb ed="#V" n="10" break="no"/>mus nullo saciatur lucro.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e546"> 
             / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e630">Libro. 19. e. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="11"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e548">Desunt inopie multa: auaritie omnia. In
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>nullum auarus bonus est: in se pessimus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e556">
               <lb ed="#V" n="13"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e644">9. e.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e560">Nulla auaritia sine pena est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e564"> 
         / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e652">Libro
        <lb ed="#V" n="14"/>20. et fina. e. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e566">Qui multum habet plus 
               cu<lb ed="#V" n="15" break="no"/>pit. Neminem pecunia diuitem fecit. Imo
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/>etiam nulli non maiorem sui cupiditatem
        <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>incussit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e578"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e670">6. e.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e580">Quanta dementia est heredis
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/>sui res procurare: et sibi denegare omnia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e587">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e682">Idem de breuitate vite:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e591">Solius temporis
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/>honesta auaritia est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e597"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e692">Idem de 
               consolatio<lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>ne ad helbiam matrem:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e599">Auaritia est 
               vehe<lb ed="#V" n="22" break="no"/>mentissima humani generis pestis. 
               Cupidi<lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>tati nihil satis est: nature satis est etiam 
               pa<lb ed="#V" n="24" break="no"/>rum. Quicquid desiderio quod non ex inopia
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/>sed vitio nascitur congesseris: non finis erit
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>cupiditatis: sed gradus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e616"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e713">Idem de 
               natura<lb ed="#V" n="27" break="no"/>libus questionis: lib. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e618">Auaritia quicquid
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>omnibus abstulit sibiipsi negat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e626"> 
         / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e726">Idem in
        <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>prouerbiis:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e628">Negandi causa auaro nunquam
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>deficit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e636">
               <lb ed="#V" n="31"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e741">Lucanus libro. 3</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e640">Ferram mortemque 
               ti<lb ed="#V" n="32" break="no"/>mere Auri nescit amor.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e646">
               <lb ed="#V" n="33"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e754">Frontinus: li. 4. et fi. t. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e650">Casilini 
               obsiden<lb ed="#V" n="34" break="no"/>te hannibale tantam inopiam perpessi sunt
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/>vt centum denariis murem venisse 
               prodi<lb ed="#V" n="36" break="no"/>tum memorie sit: eiusque venditorem fame 
               pe<lb ed="#V" n="37" break="no"/>riisse: emptorem autem vixisse.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e663">
               <lb ed="#V" n="38"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e772">Iuuenalis: lib. 4. saty. 3. et finali.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e667">Non propter vitam faciunt patrimonia quidam
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>Sed vicio ceci propter patrimonia viuunt</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e675">
               <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e786">Libro. 5. et fina. saty. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e679">Crescit amor numi quantum ipsa pecunia crescit
        <lb ed="#V" n="43"/>Nec plura venena.
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>Miscuit aut ferro crassatum sepius vllum.
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>humane mentis vicium: quam seua cuprido <!--227.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>Indomiti census. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e698">
               <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e811">Lex dige. ti. de vulga. et pupilla. substi. l.
        <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>2. §. interdum.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e702">Improbum esse iulianus 
               exi<lb ed="#V" n="49" break="no"/>stimat eum qui sollicitus est de viuentis 
               he<lb ed="#V" n="50" break="no"/>reditate.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e712">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e828">Marcialis cocus l. vndique suscepto. c. 3.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e716">Non sibi non aliis prodest dum viuit auarus.
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>Et prodest aliis et sibi dum moritur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e724">
               <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e842">Maximianus:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e728">Auri cecus amor natiuum
        <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>vincit amorem.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e732">
        <lb ed="#V" n="56"/>¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e855">Hieronymus in prologo principii biblie:</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e736">Non habet auaro tam deest quod habet quam quod
        <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>non habet.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e740">
               <lb ed="#V" n="59"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e869">Auctor l. de for. hone. vite. c. 2</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e744">Non que
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>apud te habes tanquam aliena seruabis: sed pro
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>te tanquam tua et dispones et vtaris</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e753">
               <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e883">Ambrosius de ossiciis: li. 2. c. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e757">Auaratia
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>perfidie vicina est.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e763">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e895">Cecilius de beata vita: li. 4.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e767">Tres sunt 
               af<lb ed="#V" n="65" break="no"/>fectus qui homines in omnia facinora 
               precipi<lb ed="#V" n="66" break="no"/>tes agunt: ira: cupiditas: libido.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e775">
               <lb ed="#V" n="67"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e909">Prudentius de psicomachia. c. 8.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e779">Parcit
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>ne propriis amor inficiatus habendi.
        <lb ed="#V" n="69"/>Pignoribus spoliatque suos fames ipsa natos</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e787">
               <lb ed="#V" n="70"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e923">Fulgentius. lib. 2. fabula. 13.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e791">Auarus in
        <lb ed="#V" n="71"/>tantum stultus est: vt sibi prodesse non norit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e797">
               <lb ed="#V" n="72"/>
               / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e936">Libro. 3 f. 16.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e801">Cupiditas nouit habere:
        <lb ed="#V" n="73"/>non nouit frui.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e807">
               <lb ed="#V" n="74"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e948">Cato. c. 5. et fi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e811">Utere quesitis opibus: 
               fu<lb ed="#V" n="75" break="no"/>ge nomen auari.
        <lb ed="#V" n="76"/>Quid tibi diuitie si pauper semper abundas.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e820">
               <lb ed="#V" n="77"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e962">Boetius de consolatione: lib. 2. c. 9.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="78"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e824" source="http://scta.info/resource/hy7y6y-d1e59-d1e239@66-71">Auaritia semper odiosos: claros largitas
        <lb ed="#V" n="79"/>facit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e832"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e974">Capitulo. 10.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="80"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e834">Seuior ignibus ethne.
        <lb ed="#V" n="81"/>Feruens amor ardet habendi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e842">
               <lb ed="#V" n="82"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e988">Libro. 3. c. 5. Auartitie nihil satis est.
        <lb ed="#V" n="83"/>Capitulo. 6.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e846">Quamuis fluente diues auri gurgite:
        <lb ed="#V" n="84"/>Non expleturas cogat auarus opes.
        <lb ed="#V" n="85"/>Oneretque baccis colla rubri littoris
        <lb ed="#V" n="86"/>Ruraque centeno scindat optima boue.
        <lb ed="#V" n="87"/>Nec cura mordax deserit superstitem.
        <lb ed="#V" n="88"/>Defunctumque leues non comitantur opes</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e863">
               <lb ed="#V" n="89"/>
                / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1011">Idem de disciplina scholarium: lib. 3</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="90"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e867">Fame nouerca est adunca tenacitas. <!--228.xml-->
        <pb ed="#V" n="95-r"/>
                  <cb ed="#V" n="a"/>
               </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e879">
               <lb ed="#V" n="1"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1030">Cassiodorus epistolarum: li. 3. e. 11.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e883">
               Aua<lb ed="#V" n="2" break="no"/>ra fuge.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e889"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1040">Li. 12. et fi. e. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e891">Reginam illam 
               pro<lb ed="#V" n="3" break="no"/>catium vitiorum auaritiam fuge: cui cuncta
        <lb ed="#V" n="4"/>crimina detestabili denotatione famulantur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="5"/>Auaritia arma suscipit ex talentis: et per 
               dul<lb ed="#V" n="6" break="no"/>cedinem superat quos amata deceptione 
               ca<lb ed="#V" n="7" break="no"/>ptiuat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e906"> 
          / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1058">Idem de charitate seu dilectione
        <lb ed="#V" n="8"/>dei. c. 5.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e908">Hydropici more qui plus bibendo
        <lb ed="#V" n="9"/>plus sitit: pecunie cupiditas ex 
               multiplica<lb ed="#V" n="10" break="no"/>tione grandescit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e918">
               <lb ed="#V" n="11"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1075">Auctor l. qui dicitur pamphylus. in fi. in
        <lb ed="#V" n="12"/>apilogo:</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e922">Dum bibit hydropicus magis et 
               si<lb ed="#V" n="13" break="no"/>tit et cupit vndam. Sic magis exardet 
               sem<lb ed="#V" n="14" break="no"/>per auaritia.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e932">
               <lb ed="#V" n="15"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1092">Auctor l. qui dicitur facetus. c. 10 et fina.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="16"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e936">Cui sua non prosunt alii conseruat habenda.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e942">
               <lb ed="#V" n="17"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1104">Bernardus. l de improbatione vitiorum. c. 6.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="18"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e946">Pestis auaritie fragili viget in muliere.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e952">
               <lb ed="#V" n="19"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1117">Andreas ad gualterium de amore: lib. 2.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="20"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e956">Omnis probitas de auaritie admixtione 
               sup<lb ed="#V" n="21" break="no"/>primitur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e964">
               <lb ed="#V" n="22"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1131">Gualterius de castellione: lib. i.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e968">Non 
               mu<lb ed="#V" n="23" break="no"/>rus non arma ducem vitantur auarum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e976">
        <lb ed="#V" n="24"/> <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1143">Libro 8. et antepenultimo.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="25"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e978">Quid tibi diuitiis opus est: que semper auaro
        <lb ed="#V" n="26"/>Esuriem pariunt: quanto tibi plura parasti:
        <lb ed="#V" n="27"/>Tanto plura cupis et habendis acrius ardes.
        <lb ed="#V" n="28"/>Sicque famen faciens defectum copia mittit</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e986">
               <lb ed="#V" n="29"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1161">Mattheus vindocinensis de hysto. tobie
        <lb ed="#V" n="30"/>c. 25.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e990">Desit auaritie fex cui sua deesse 
               stupe<lb ed="#V" n="31" break="no"/>scit. Copia nuda sitis ebria plena fames.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e998">
               <lb ed="#V" n="32"/>
               / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1176">Capitulo 30.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1002">Te non excruciet census 
               si<lb ed="#V" n="33" break="no"/>tis ebria: cuius Pullulat ex gustu 
               multipli<lb ed="#V" n="34" break="no"/>cata fames.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1010"> 
         / <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1188">Idem in poetria. partis. i. c. 19.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="35"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1012">Aurum roma sitit: dantes amat absque datiuo.
        <lb ed="#V" n="36"/>Accusatiuo roma fauere negat.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1020">
               <lb ed="#V" n="37"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1203">Heinricus samariensis: li. i. partis. 2.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1024">Ipsa 
               cu<lb ed="#V" n="38" break="no"/>pit mundi venalis curia pape.
        <lb ed="#V" n="39"/>Prostat et infirmat cetera membra caput.
        <lb ed="#V" n="40"/>Sacrum cerne nephas nostro prudentius euo
        <lb ed="#V" n="41"/>Uenditur in turpi conditione foro
        <lb ed="#V" n="42"/>Crisma sacrum: sacer ordo altaria sacra 
               sa<lb ed="#V" n="43" break="no"/>crata Dona. quid hoc vltra venditur ipse deus.
        <lb ed="#V" n="44"/>Si foret vt quondam lucretia casta crumena:
        <lb ed="#V" n="45"/>Cum sibi porrigitur cedet auara tibi. <!--228.xml-->
        <cb ed="#V" n="b"/>
                  <lb ed="#V" n="46"/>Uenditur o dolor omnificis sententia nummis
        <lb ed="#V" n="47"/>Iudicium pium copia frangit opum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1054">
               <lb ed="#V" n="48"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1239">Gaufridus in poetria. c. 101.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1058">Liber is est
        <lb ed="#V" n="49"/>vitiis qui non inseruit abundans.
        <lb ed="#V" n="50"/>Cui satis est quod habet: pauper qui plus cupit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1066">
               <lb ed="#V" n="51"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1253">Iacobus beneuentanus. c. 11.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="52"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1070">Hydropico similis nunquam saciatur auarus.
        <lb ed="#V" n="53"/>Infelix requie nocte dieque caret.
        <lb ed="#V" n="54"/>Custos non dominus estat auarus opum.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1081">
               <lb ed="#V" n="55"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1269">Auctor l. qui incipit astrolabi.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1085">
               Hydropi<lb ed="#V" n="56" break="no"/>co similis nemo nisi diues auarus.
        <lb ed="#V" n="57"/>Ex lucro lueri multiplicando sitim.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1093">
               <lb ed="#V" n="58"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1283">Auctor l. de moribus medicorum. c. 21.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="59"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1097">Hydropico similis omnis auarus adest.
        <lb ed="#V" n="60"/>Non gaudet pertis: quia tangere parta veretur.
        <lb ed="#V" n="61"/>Ne sibi deficiant: pauper auarus eget.
        <lb ed="#V" n="62"/>Est similis talpe metuenti mandere terram.
        <lb ed="#V" n="63"/>Ne sibi deficiat: sic perit ipsa fame.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1111">
               <lb ed="#V" n="64"/>
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1303">Montenarius in luna cleri. c. 46.</ref>
        <lb ed="#V" n="65"/> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1115">Furari famulos dominus compellit auarus.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-d1e1121">
               <lb ed="#V" n="66"/>
                ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Rd1e1316">Prouerb. metricum. extraord l. vag.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d74978-Qd1e1125">
               Presu<lb ed="#V" n="67" break="no"/>sulis albini: vel martyris ossa ruffini:
        <lb ed="#V" n="68"/>Rome si quis habet vertere cuncta potest.</quote>
            </p>
